<TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=160 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=2>

<!--HOT NEWS BUTTON------------------------------------------------------------------------>
<!--TR><TD align=center bgcolor=FFBC2A>
<font face="arial" size=+0><a href="hotnews.html#">Hot News</a>
</TD></TR-->

<!--MORE INFO BUTTON------------------------------------------------------------------------>
<TR><TD align=center bgcolor=FF595B>
<font face="arial" size=+0><a href="repromi.html">More Information</a>
</TD></TR>

<!--CAMPAIGN HISTORY BUTTON------------------------------------------------------------------------>
<!--TR><TD align=center bgcolor=AAAAEE>
<font face="arial" size=+0><a href="repro.html">Campaign History</a>
</TD></TR-->


</TABLE>


<END OF LEFT COLUMN---------------------------------------------------------->

<TD WIDTH=400 VALIGN=TOP>
<TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=100% HEIGHT=70>
<TR><TD  VALIGN=TOP>
<FONT SIZE=+2 FACE="MS SERIF">R E P R O C E S S I N G</FONT>
</TD>
</TR></TABLE>

<TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=390><TR><TD>

<FONT SIZE=+0 FACE="MS SERIF">
<P><B>Reprocessing plutonium: A dead end</B>

<P>While producing electricity, nuclear power stations create plutonium.  The plutonium is 
contained in the irradiated nuclear fuel (INF) resulting from operating a nuclear reactor.

<BR>In addition to the separated plutonium and uranium, reprocessing creates a 
tremendous volume of radioactive waste - chemicals, equipment and other 
materials involved in reprocessing,   generating a volume of waste as
much as 189 times greater than that contained in the original irradiated fuel.   

<P><B>Greenpeace believes that the separation, transportation 
and use of plutonium must immediately be stopped.</B>
</FONT>
</TD></TR></TABLE>
 
</TD>


</TR></TABLE>


</body></html>



