<HTML>
<HEAD>

<TITLE>Greenpeace - SmILE</TITLE>


</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="./../gfx/bgtile2.gif" LINK="#330000" ALINK="#993300" VLINK="#993300" TEXT="#FFFFFF">
<TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=570 HEIGHT=64>
<TR>
<TD>
<A HREF="./../index.html"><IMG ALIGN=MIDDLE SRC="./../gfx/climicon.gif" ALT="Greenpeace Climate Crisis" WIDTH="102" HEIGHT="42" BORDER="0"></A>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<TABLE CELLPADDING=10 WIDTH=580>
<TR>
<TD COLSPAN=3 ALIGN=CENTER>
<IMG SRC="fstitle.gif" ALT="SmILE - Greenpeace" WIDTH="350" HEIGHT="96" BORDER="0"></TD>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN=TOP>
	<TABLE BORDER=1 CELLPADDING=5>
	<TR>
	<TD BGCOLOR="#EFBD10" VALIGN=TOP HEIGHT=100%>
	<FONT SIZE=+1>
	<P>
	<A HREF="./tech/table.html"><B>Technical<BR>
	Information (Table)</B></A>
	</P>
	<P><A HREF="./bkgrnd/index.html"><B>Background<BR>
	Information</B></A>
	</P>
	<P>
	<A HREF="./firstpix/index.html"><B>Pictorial</B></A>
	</P>
	<P>
	<A HREF="./faq/index.html"><B>Frequently<BR>
	Asked<BR>
	Questions<BR></B></A>
	</P>
	<P>
	<B><A HREF="./dirty/index.html">Feature:<BR>
	The Dirty Track of the Car Industry</A></B>
	<P>
	<A HREF="./tech/index.html"><B>
	 Report:
	 <BR>
	 Technical<BR>
	Information</B></A>
	</P>
	</TD>
	</TR>
	</TABLE>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN=TOP>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="+1" COLOR="#EFBD10"><B>E</B></FONT>ven the most devoted car lover would admit that the car is not good news
for the environment.  The transport sector is responsible for  22%  of the
world's greenhouse gas emissions,  and cars  contribute  80% of this. We
must reduce the ecological impact of the global car culture upon our
biosphere. Car manufacturers have until now failed to take even the first
step in the right direction - that is  the production of the most efficient
vehicle possible using existing technology.
</P>

<P>
Greenpeace has taken that first step by producing the SmILE, a modified
Renault Twingo, which is almost 50% more efficient than its conventional
counterpart and other cars of similar size.
</P>

<P>
Find out in these pages, why and how  Greenpeace - the world's largest activist
environmental organization - is seemingly promoting a car technology,
called the SmILE Concept, in order to protect the environment.
</P>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN=CENTER VALIGN=TOP>
<IMG SRC="splash2.gif" ALT="Small - Intelligent - Light - Efficient" WIDTH="95" HEIGHT="373" BORDER="0">
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
