<BR><font size=+1 face="arial">GREENPEACE STOPS GENETICALLY ENGINEERED SOYBEAN DESTINED FOR EUROPE ON
     MISSISSIPPI RIVER </font>

</td></tr>
</table>

<blockquote>

<p><b><font size=+2>Arrests as protestors confront grain giant</font></b><br>
<p><center>
</center>
<p><b>MISSISSIPPI RIVER, LOUISIANNA, NOVEMBER 19TH 1996 </b>


  

<P>&nbsp<img border=0 width=20 height=20 src="../icons/bioact.gif"> Greenpeace activists aboard the  'MV Greenpeace' sailed up the Mississippi River to confront food industry giant Cargill at their
     grain facility in Laplace , 60 miles outside of New Orleans. 

<br clear=all><br>

<a href="../pics/ge17.jpg"><img hspace=15 vspace=10 width=100 height=150 border=0 src="../thumbs/ge17t.jpg"></a>

<a href="../pics/ge18.jpg"><img hspace=15 vspace=10 width=100 height=150 border=0 src="../thumbs/ge18t.jpg"></a>

<a href="../pics/ge19.jpg"><img hspace=15 vspace=10 width=100 height=150 border=0 src="../thumbs/ge19t.jpg"></a>

<br clear=all>

<P>&nbsp<img border=0 width=20 height=20 src="../icons/bioact.gif"> Activists in inflatable boats identified a ship being loaded with
     Monsanto's genetically engineered soybeans and "branded" the ship with bright yellow posters that read 'X - Genetic
     Experiment'. 

<br clear=all><br>

<a href="../pics/ge20.jpg"><img hspace=15 vspace=10 width=150 height=100 border=0 src="../thumbs/ge20t.jpg"></a>

<a href="../pics/ge21.jpg"><img hspace=15 vspace=10 width=150 height=100 border=0 src="../thumbs/ge21t.jpg"></a>

<a href="../pics/ge22.jpg"><img hspace=15 vspace=10 width=150 height=100 border=0 src="../thumbs/ge22t.jpg"></a>

<br clear=all>

<P>&nbsp<img border=0 width=20 height=20 src="../icons/bioact.gif"> Meanwhile six other activists climbed onto the grain facility, preventing the loading of the genetically engineered
     soybeans. 




<P>&nbsp<img border=0 width=20 height=20 src="../icons/bioact.gif"> Five activists, Peter Bradley, Anibal Rivera, Monica Rhode, David DeRosa and Tanya
     Whitford were arrested in the course of the action, charged with criminal trespass and held over night at St. John the Baptist Parish until released with a with $3,000 bond. 
  

<p><br>
