<HEAD>
<TITLE>Press release: 12th August 1996 - SPANISH FISHERMEN AND GREENPEACE EJECT  ILLEGAL ITALIAN
DRIFTNETTERS FROM THE BALEARIC SEA </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="CCCCFC" TEXT="130036" LINK="D51C27" VLINK="970000" ALINK="E200A9">
<table border=1 cellpadding=5 width=100%><tr><td>

<a href="../fish/index.html#fish"><img border=0 align=left WIDTH=80 HEIGHT=67 src="../icons/oce01t.gif"></a>
<a href="newsindx.html#drift02"><img align=right  border=0 width=60 height=60 src="../icons/bionews.gif"></a>
</td></tr></table>

<blockquote>

<P><B>SPANISH FISHERMEN AND GREENPEACE EJECT  ILLEGAL ITALIAN
DRIFTNETTERS FROM THE BALEARIC SEA </B>
<P><B>Balearic Sea, Western Mediterranean - 12th August 1996</B>
 
<P>Last night at 12:30, the MV Arctic Sunrise approached the end
of a driftnet  seven miles long. 

<P>Hours before, Spanish
fishermen had radioed the net's position, as was 
agreed during the meeting held with them onboard the Greenpeace ship Arctic 
Sunrise  on Sunday afternoon.
 
<P>Around 20 Spanish driftneters tied along the net, mantaining a 
distance of 200 meters between each vessel.  Next, three inflatables 
from the Arctic Sunrise went into the area.  An activist tied wooden fish and 
turtles to the italian net  to make the hauling operation more dificult.

<P>Spanish driftneters, upset because of the continuing situation with illegal driftnets, took the net, hauling it aboard their boats. In the net 
 a sea turtle and a swordfish were found in the net ( and then released alive ). <P>Some Spanish
longline fishermen cut the illegal Italian driftnet and took away  pieces of it which were 
left in the water.
 
<P>The Italian driftnetter -the name of which could not be identified- 
then escaped from the area.
 
<P>In the meantime, some longliners sailed to another net 2 nm away from the first one and tied  up to it. The driftnetter 
(SEBASTIANO ACIPLATANI) started to haul quickly. Greenpeace 
inflatables were trying to stop the operation, and Italian 

fishermen threw potatoes and other objects at them, shouting 
and using abusive language.
 
<P>The tension grew. The illegal Italian driftnetter shot four bengal lights against 
environmenatlists and fishing boats. Some crews almost came to blows, 
and the situation was quite dangerous. In the meantime GP 
inflatables were asking for a peaceful protest. Eventually, this 
second driftnetter abandoned the area.
 
<P>" Both our fleet and the environmentalists want the total elimination 
of the driftnets. We want the Spanish government to pressure 
Italy to dismantle this fleet and we want the European Union to 
ban this type of fishing" said the skipper of one of the 
longiners who participated in the action.
 

<BR><BR><HR><BR> 
<P>FOR FURTHER INFORMATION CONTACT:

<P>Alessandro Gianni on 00 31 653 9117 73

<P> Helene Bours on 00 3241 68 68 51 

<P>James Gillies on 00 31 6 5323


<BR><BR><HR><BR>

<B>
<P>NEW ADDRESS:
<P>Keizersgracht 176
<P>1016 DW AMSTERDAM
<P>THE NETHERLANDS
<P>phone: 31 (20) 523 6222/ 524 9548 (direct line)
<P>fax: 31 (20) 523 6200
</B>
</blockquote>

</body></html>




