<HEAD>
<TITLE>DANISH FISHERMEN THREATEN TO SINK GREENPEACE SHIP, M.V. SIRIUS</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="CCCCFC" TEXT="130036" LINK="D51C27" VLINK="970000" ALINK="E200A9">
<table border=1 cellpadding=5 width=100%><tr><td>

<a href="nsea.html"><img align=left WIDTH=60 HEIGHT= 80 src="../icons/nsea11.gif"></a>
<a href="newsindx.html"><img align=right  border=0 width=60 height=60 src="../icons/bionews.gif"></a>
</td></tr></table>

<P><B>DANISH FISHERMEN THREATEN TO SINK GREENPEACE SHIP, M.V. SIRIUS
 </B>
  
<P>FRIDAY, JUNE 28TH 1996 





<P>At seven o'clock this morning we've launched two inflatbles again
to start messing around with the Scottish Omega B. This was the
first vessel we did actions on last sunday. They then left the
Wee Bankie. 
<P>Omega B asked for assistance and the Jannie replied
that all Danish vessels were standby for help. HMS Shetland
called on the radio for an inspection of the Omega B. 
<P>We changed
to the Jannie. The fisheries protection people went over to the
Jannie as well. Jannie was hauling it's net and there not a
single fish in it. It seems like they've fished out most of the
sandeels by now. The fleet is very scattered over the banks to
find the last sandeels.


<P>8.45 hrs: 'this is vessel Pernille for Sirius, will you give up
your actions in the area if not we are going to sink you now.'
Then Pernille and Jannie came after us. They are getting very
close, we can see the men on the fore deck ready with the
grappling hooks and flares. For entering, to tear up the three
inflatables still on deck? All paople are on deck wearing life
jackets and survival suits waiting for things to happen. I'll
send this out now and go on deck too.



<B><P>Later radio exchanges between the Danish industrial fishing fleet, fisheries protection vessel HMS Shetland and
Greenpeace vessel M.V. Sirius:


</B>

<P>

<B>8.55 hrs</B>

<P>'This is Pernille Kim fir Sirius. If you wanna save your ship .
We will sink it now and all our collegues are coming. If you
wanna save your ship and your crew and all the members on your
ship you are requested to cancel your mission immedeately. Then
we let your ship and the people go.
This time we've got you.
OK you have been warned.'


<P>Then the vessels Pernille Kim and Jannie started the chase, the
crew ready on the fore deck with grappling hooks etc..


<P><B>9.55 hrs</B>

<P>HMS Shetland for vessel Jannie
'You're now inside British territorial limits. Your current
actions are prejudicial to good order and peace woithin British
territorial seas. Therefore we ask you to call off your present
pursuit of the vessels in front of you.'


<P>Jannie: 'OK we stop.'


<P><B>10.00 hrs</B>
The chase is off, but the whole fishing fleet has stopped fishing
and is now coming our direction.

<BR><BR><HR><BR>
 

<B>FOR FURTHER INFORMATION CONTACT:

<P> STEFAN FLOTHMANN OR PHIL AIKMAN ON THE 
MV SIRIUS 040 605187 OR SAT PHONE ($US10 PER MINUTE) 00-874 130 
0144. 
<P>OR 
<P>CHRIS ROSE ON 0831-388 503 OR 01273-486 476 
<P>OR 
<P>JON 
WALTER AT GREENPEACE COMMUNICATIONS 0171-833 0600
 </B>

