</td></tr></table>

<P><B>GREENPEACE SHIP RAMMED BY DANISH INDUSTRIAL FISHING VESSEL 
 </B>
  
<P>MONDAY, JUNE 24TH 1996 RELEASE 2
 
<P>The Greenpeace vessel MV Sirius was rammed by a Danish industrial 
fishing boat during a confrontation with the industrial fishing fleet , near Edinburgh off  the Scottish 
North Sea coast. 
 
<P>The Danish vessel the Mette Eliasen,  rammed the MV Sirius at the bow at about 10 am. There was 
only minor damage thanks to the evasive taken by the MV Sirius captain. 
 
<P>A group of  seven Danish industrial fishing vessels remain on the Wee Bankie area, off the Firth of 
Forth but have stopped fishing.  
 

<P>Earlier today Danish fishing boats fired flares at Greenpeace inflatables and across the bow of the MV 
Sirius as the activists attempted to stop a Scottish industrial fishing vessel from fishing on the Wee 
Bankie. The Wee Bankie is a major feeding ground for commercial fish stocks,  dolphins and birds. 


