<TITLE>GREENPEACE CONFRONTS DANISH INDUSTRIAL FISHING FLEET</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="CCCCFC" TEXT="130036" LINK="D51C27" VLINK="970000" ALINK="E200A9">
<table border=1 cellpadding=5 width=100%><tr><td>

<a href="nsea.html"><img align=left WIDTH=60 HEIGHT= 80 src="../icons/nsea11.gif"></a>
<a href="newsindx.html"><img align=right  border=0 width=60 height=60 src="../icons/bionews.gif"></a>
</td></tr></table>

<P><B>GREENPEACE CONFRONTS DANISH INDUSTRIAL FISHING FLEET
 </B>
  
<P>SUNDAY, JUNE 23rd 1996 release 2

 
 
 
 

<P>
At 14:45 today activists from the Greenpeace ship MV Sirius
attempted to stop the operation of the Danish industrial fishing
boat "Jannie" in the ecologically sensitive area, the Wee Bankie,
off the Scottish Firth of Forth.
     

<P>The Greenpeace action involves swimmers using an inflatable oil
boom, placing themselves in the path of the oncoming fishing
vessel. The action is ongoing as of 15:20 hours.
 
<P>Last year mainly Danish industrial fishing vessels caught 40 000
tonnes of sandeels from the Wee Bankie, an area important for
feeding birds, dolphins and minke whales. This morning a similar
action against the British ship "Omega B" was successful.
     
 <BR><BR><HR><BR>
 
<B><P>FOR FURTHER INFORMATION CONTACT:

<P> Chris Rose on 01273-486476
or MV Sirius (Stefan Flothmann/Phil Aikman) on 0402-605187 or sat
phone ($US10 per minute) 00 874 130 0144
<P> 
or
<P>Greenpeace Information Office, Dunbar on 01368-865982            </B>


 
