GREENPEACE VESSEL SOLO.</H5>



<P>INTRO: Greenpeace Captain Ulf Birgander made the usual security

announcement that we broadcast every 4 hours, naming the Pintail,

its cargo, its route and asking ships to give wide berth to the

Pintail. 



<P>Start Transcript:



<P>(BA) Solo, this is Brazilian Airforce, over;

<br>(GP) Brazilian Airforce, this is Greenpeace vessel Solo, Good

afternoon, over;

<br>(BA) Channel 10, please

<br>(BA on Ch.10) This is Brazilian Airforce, over

<br>(GP) Good afternoon Brazilian Aircraft, this is Motor Vessel

Solo, over;

<br>(BA) Good afternoon, Brazilian Airforce patrol request, request, 

take care, take care [of] our friend, please;

<br>(GP) Yes, we will certainly take care of your friend, we will

follow her on a safe distance, and will inform all the countries

and all vessels in vicinity of her highly dangerous cargo.

<br>(BA) The Brazil thank you for your job;

<br>(GP) Thank you very much;

<br>(BA) Stand by Channel 16, over;.

<br>(GP) Greenpeace vessel Solo back to channel 16.



