<head>Date:    SUN 16-APR-95 06:04:08 GMT
Subject: Solo Update 04/16/95   0600GMT DAY53


<H4>PACIFIC PINTAIL STEAMS ON TOWARD JAPAN</H4>

</head><body>

<P>The Pacific Pintail with its 14 tonnes of radioactive waste is in position
(0600 GMT) is 26 degrees 08 minutes North, and 167 degrees and 32 minutes
East. The Pintail's course is 285 degrees and the ship's speed is 13 Knots.
For distances to Pacific Islands please see enclosed table.

<HR>Pacific State   City/Island    Distance/Direction relative to PP's course
<HR>
Mutsu Ogawara   Japan           1,575  miles, 15 degrees right of PP 
<br>Tokyo           Japan           1,545  miles, 5 degrees right of PP 
<br>Marshall Isl.   Bikini            870  miles, 100 degrees left of PP 
<br>F.S. Micronesia Pohnpei         1,265  miles, 85 degrees left of PP 
<br>Nauru           Nauru Island    1,595  miles, 105 degrees left of PP 
<br>Guam            Guam            1,540  miles, 50 degrees left of PP 
<br>Solomon Isl.    Honiara         2,180  miles, 95 degrees left of PP

<P>Media updates from the Solo are sent out on a daily basis at approximately
0600 GMT and 0800 lt. If additional information on the Pacific Pintail's
voyage or it's cargo of plutonium waste is required, please contact Bas Bruyne
on the Solo (phone:++ 872-1301166), or Karen Richardson at Greenpeace UK
(phone: ++44-171-226-3151). Photo, video, or other media requests should be
made to Blair Palese or Mark Warford at Greenpeace Communications (phone:
++44-171-8330-600).  

