<A NAME = notef85></A> <A HREF = "#textf85"> [85]</A><A NAME = Notef85></A> UNCLOS Art. 220(7)<P>
<A NAME = notef86></A> <A HREF = "#textf86"> [86]</A><A NAME = Notef86></A> UNCLOS Art. 221(1). "Maritime casualty" is defined as a collision of vessels, 
stranding or other incident of navigation or other occurrence on board a vessel or external to it resulting in material 
damage or imminent threat of material damage to a vessel or cargo: Art. 221(2)<P>
<A NAME = notef87></A> <A HREF = "#textf87"> [87]</A><A NAME = Notef87></A> UNCLOS Art. 19, TSC Art. 14(4)<P>
<A NAME = notef88></A> <A HREF = "#textf88"> [88]</A><A NAME = Notef88></A><I> Basel Convention on the Control of Transboundary Movements of Hazardous 
