<h3>Current Nuclear Campaign Information</h3></center>
<center>
<font size=+1>
Please read the new Campaign Bulletin <a href="/~usa/reports/nuclear/stop_plutonium/index.html">"Stop Plutonium"</a> which exposes the dangers of radioactive waste transports!<p></font>
<a href="/~usa/reports/nuclear/stop_plutonium/index.html"><img src="/~usa/reports/nuclear/stop_plutonium/pix/stopluto.gif" width=504 height=100 ALT="Stop Plutonium" border=0></a><p>
<font size=-1>For additional information about this campaign, please see the frequently updated Greenpeace International
<a href="/~comms/no.nukes"><b>"no.nukes -- pathways to destruction" web site</b></a> which has a wealth
of material explaining the civil and military nuclear complex and Greenpeace's position on:
<ul><b>
<li><a href="/~comms/nukes/ctbt/read10.html">World nuclear arsenals</a>;</li>
<li><a href="/~comms/nukes/ctbt/read3.html">Selected accidents involving nuclear weapons</a> 1950-1993;</li>
<li><a href="/~comms/nukes/ctbt/read6.html">Stopping nuclear testing -- CTBT now</a> (April 1996);</li>
<li><a href="/~comms/nukes/ctbt/read8.html">Nuclear weapons testing countries</a> (April 1996);</li>
<li><a href="/~comms/nukes/ctbt/read9.html">History of nuclear weapons testing</a>  (April 1996);</li>
<li><a href="/~comms/nukes/ctbt/read11.html">China's nuclear weapons and testing program</a> (April 1996);</li>
<li><a href="/~comms/no.nukes/waste01.html">Radioactive nuclear waste</a> (February 1996);</li>
<li><a href="/~comms/no.nukes/minfabmi.html">Uranium mining factsheet</a>;</li>
<li><a href="/~comms/no.nukes/react01.html">The failure of nuclear power briefing paper</a>;</li>
<li><a href="/~comms/nukes/chernob/rep01.html">Nuclear safety and the G7 - a contradiction in terms?</a>;</li>
<li><a href="/~comms/nukes/chernob/rep02.html">Calendar of nuclear accidents and events</a>;</li> 
<li><a href="/~comms/nukes/chernob/read25.html">Chernobyl: ten years after  - causes, consequences, solutions</a>;</li>
<li><a href="/~comms/nukes/chernob/read8.html">Nuclear Power World Status Report 1996</a>;</li>
<li><a href="/~comms/no.nukes/transhn.html">Map of proposed nuclear waste transport</a>.</li>
</b></ul></font>
<p>
<font size=+1>Another recent Greenpeace USA report, <a href="/~usa/reports/nuclear/amchitka/index.html">"Nuclear Flashback,"</a> reveals the lethal legacy of U.S. nuclear tests at Amchitka Island, Alaska in 1971.<p></font>
<a href="/~usa/reports/nuclear/amchitka/index.html"><img src="/~usa/reports/nuclear/amchitka/pix/flshbck2.gif" border=0></a><p>
<table width=80% cellpadding=15 border=3><tr><td>
<center><font size=+1>Greenpeace was founded 25 years ago to protest those very same nuclear tests in Alaska.<p>
On September 24, 1996 the <b>Comprehensive Test Ban Treaty</b> was signed by President Clinton at the United Nations. This victory represents many years 
of hard work as you can see in this <a href="timeline.html">timeline</a> of our history of protests against nuclear testing.</font></center>
</td></tr></table></center>
<p>
<center><blink><font size=+2><b>ACTION ALERTS!</b></font></blink></center>
<center><img src="pix/nukewind.gif" width=129 height=119 ALT="nuke power morph to wind power"></center>
<ul>
<p>
<li><a href="/~usa/updates/96_3_29.html">Consumers may be forced to produce bomb
material!</a> Stop nuclear utilities from promoting proliferation by using fuel made from
weapons-grade plutonium!</li>
